# React Patterns

## Structure

- DRY: render repeated UI from arrays with `.map()` instead of copy-paste JSX
- Pass props explicitly (e.g. `title`, `excerpt`, `author`) � avoid `{ article }` object props
- Extract long Tailwind strings into class constant objects (e.g. `articleCardClasses`)
- Use feature folders for domain logic (`src/features/blog/`)

## Conditional Classes

Prefer `if/else` over ternary for conditional class names:

```jsx
let tabClass = 'rounded-full px-4 py-2 text-sm'
if (isActive) {
  tabClass += ' bg-neutral-900 text-white'
} else {
  tabClass += ' text-neutral-600 hover:bg-neutral-100'
}
```

## Variants

Use a `variant` prop for responsive or layout differences (e.g. `variant="desktop"` | `"mobile"`).

## Components

- Use shadcn/ui primitives from `@/components/ui/*` before writing custom elements
- Use `Button`, `Input`, etc. with CVA variants where applicable
